This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a method for improving the training of Bayesian neural networks using self-stabilising priors. The paper also discusses the challenges of training deep architectures and dealing with large weight variances, which are common issues in machine learning. Additionally, the paper mentions variational inference, which is a popular technique in machine learning. 

The paper could also belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as Bayesian neural networks are a type of AI model and the paper proposes a method for improving their training. 

The sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possibility as the paper focuses on neural networks and their training. 

The sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is another possibility as the paper mentions noisy settings, which could be relevant to computer vision tasks. 

Finally, the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely possibility as the paper discusses signal propagation theory, which is relevant to control systems. However, the focus of the paper is on machine learning and neural networks, so cs.SY is less likely than the other sub-categories mentioned.
